===Noun===
'''bumper'''  (''plural:'' '''[[bumpers]]''')
# {{cricket}}: A [[bouncer]].
# {{automotive}}: [[Part]]s at the [[front]] and [[back]] of a [[vehicle]] which are meant to [[absorb]] the [[impact]] of a [[collision]].
# Any mechanical device used to absorb an impact, soften a collision, or protect against impact.
#:''The company sells screw-on rubber '''bumpers''' and feet.''
# ''(Billiards):'' The side walls of a [[pool table]].
# A drinking vessel filled to the [[brim]].
# In [[television]] or [[radio]], a short [[ditty]] or [[jingle]] used to separate a [[show]] from the [[advertisements]].
# Someone or something that [[bump]]s.

===Adjective===
'''bumper'''
# [[large|Large]]; filled to the bumpers at the top of a silo.
#: ''We harvested a '''bumper''' crop of arugula and parsnips this year.''

